# Constrai — git line-ending policy
#
# Shell scripts MUST be LF, regardless of the committer's OS. Windows clones
# can otherwise corrupt them to CRLF and break execution on the prod Linux box
# ("bad interpreter: /usr/bin/env\r" or weird syntax errors).
*.sh text eol=lf

# SQL migration files: LF (Postgres tools tolerate CRLF, but consistency
# matters for diffs).
*.sql text eol=lf

# Markdown / config files default to LF for cross-platform consistency.
*.md text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
